A: The issue is that you are not sending a line break after each write. In your case, you are sending "1", "2", and "3" without any line breaks. The BufferedReader.readLine() method reads until it encounters a line terminator, which is not provided in your case.
You can fix this by adding a line break after each write:
printWriter.write("1\n");
printWriter.write("2\n");
printWriter.write("3\n");

Alternatively, you can use println() which automatically adds a line break:
printWriter.println("1");
printWriter.println("2");
printWriter.println("3");

Both of these will ensure that each number is on its own line when read by the BufferedReader.

